text: Robert William Doran HFNZCS (5 November 1944 â€“ 13 October 2018) was a New Zealand computer scientist and historian of computing. He was Professor Emeritus of Computer Science at the University of Auckland, New Zealand. His research interests included computer architecture, parallel algorithms, and computer programming. He was also interested in the history of computing. Doran died on 13 October 2018 at home in Auckland, aged 73. ==References== Category:1944 births Category:2018 deaths Category:New Zealand scientists Category:Computer scientists
